{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require companies to hire 1 graduate per 10 employees & provide training",
        "additional_details": "Many new graduates face endless rejection due to lack of experience, trapping them in unemployment.\r\n\r\nWe ask the Government to require companies with over 20 staff to hire at least one graduate per 10 employees per year if they apply, offer 6 months paid training, and stop rejecting applicants solely for lack of experience.\r\n\r\nWe think this would break the \u201cno experience, no job\u201d cycle, improve mental health, and build a skilled workforce.",
        "background": "We want the government to require companies to hire at least one new graduate per 10 employees, provide 6 months of paid training. We think this would stop companies rejecting applicants purely due to lack of experience.",
